title: TEMECULA: Howl-o-ween fun at annual dog walk
text:
STAFF REPORT
Published: Oct. 25, 2015 Updated: 8:31 p.m. TEMECULA: Howl-o-ween fun at annual dog walk Print Photo Share Pin It 1 of 6 More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Nina Cruz dressed up her pit bull Ruby up as Captain America from “The Avengers” during the Spooktacular Halloween Dog Walk at the Promenade Temecula on Saturday. PHOTOS: FRANK BELLINO, STAFF PHOTOGRAPHER Related article » Dogs and their owners joined forces to compete for the title of best costume during the annual Spooktacular Halloween Dog Walk on Saturday at Promenade Temecula.
Spooktacular guests competed in several costume categories including:
�• 12 and under owner and pet duo/group
�• 12 and over owner and pet duo/group
�• Spookiest
�• Most Original
�• Darling Divas
�• Dashing Dudes
A costume parade, green screen photo area and pup-inspired vendors were also on hand.
All proceeds from the event will be donated to Animal Friends of the Valleys.
